# Using AI to draft a business plan
"Imagine you are an expert business strategist with the ability to articulate a company vision into a compelling business plan. I want you to ask me questions one at a time to get all the information you need. Ask me a question then STOP and wait for my answer before continuing with your next one. This is a multi-stage prompt and I want you to complete each section and deliver a response before moving on to the next one. You will remember previous information and use that to inform your responses for other sections. In each of your responses you will give me the text for a section of the business plan, followed by advice on how to improve it. If I haven't given you enough information to supply a quality response, let me know. The stages I want you to go through are the following sections of the business plan:
Company Description - An overview of the business, including its legal structure, history, location, and unique selling proposition. 
Organization and Management - Describe the company's structure and introduce key team members. Highlight relevant experience and skills.
Products and Services - Your offerings, including features, benefits, and pricing strategy. How the products or services meet market needs. Highlight the unique value proposition.
Market Analysis - Describe the target market, industry trends, and competitive landscape. Explain why the audience needs the product or service.
Marketing and Sales Strategy - Outline how you'll reach and acquire customers. Include the marketing channels, sales process, and customer retention strategies. 
Operational Plan - Explain how the business will function day-to-day, including production processes, facilities, and equipment needs. 
Executive Summary - Summarise the entire plan in 1-2 pages. Include the business concept, mission statement, key objectives, and financial highlights. Explain why there's a need for it in the market."

#  Using AI to analyze a financial report
"Play the role of a highly experienced financial analyst with the ability to extract useful information from a financial report. I want you to start by collecting the most important figures from the attached document and presenting them to me. This is a multi-stage prompt. I want you to perform the calculations I ask at each step using a chain of thought approach, give me a brief explanation of what each calculation means, and then, once you have done the calculations, give me your own analysis of the entire stage based on the results. Then ask me if I want to move on to the next stage. If you don't have the information to perform any of the calculations, tell me. DO NOT make assumptions. DO NOT fabricate numbers. It is IMPORTANT that your calculations are accurate. The calculations I need are:
STAGE 1 - PROFITABILITY: <Gross Profit Margin: (Sales Revenue - COGS) / Sales Revenue> <Operating Profit Margin: Operating Income / Revenue> <Net Profit Margin: Net Income / Revenue> <Return on Assets (ROA): Net Income / Average Total Assets> <Return on Equity (ROE): Net Income / Shareholders' Equity>
STAGE 2 - LIQUIDITY: <Current Ratio: Current Assets / Current Liabilities> <Quick Ratio: (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities> <Cash Ratio: Cash and Cash Equivalents / Current Liabilities>
STAGE 3 - EFFICIENCY: <Asset Turnover Ratio: Net Sales / Average Total Assets> <Inventory Turnover Ratio: Cost of Goods Sold / Average Inventory> <Receivables Turnover Ratio: Net Credit Sales / Average Accounts Receivable>
STAGE 4 - LEVERAGE: <Debt Ratio: Total Liabilities / Total Assets> <Debt-to-Equity Ratio: Total Liabilities / Shareholders' Equity> <Interest Coverage Ratio: Operating Income / Interest Expenses>
STAGE 5 - CASH FLOW: <Operating Cash Flow Ratio: Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities> <Cash Flow Margin: Cash Flow from Operations / Net Sales>
STAGE 6 - VALUATION: <Price-to-Earnings (P/E) Ratio: Market Price per Share / Earnings per Share> <Earnings Per Share (EPS): Net Income / Number of Outstanding Shares>"

# Using AI to create a SWOT analysis
"Take on the role of an expert strategist who can look at situations from multiple angles and spot things that most other people miss. I have {information} I would like you to create a SWOT analysis for. I want you to think about this situation from different perspectives to give me a broad view. If you need specific information that can be found on the internet, please conduct a web search and let me know where you found the information. If I haven't given you enough information to provide a valuable response, please ask questions. Deliver your response with:
- Bullet points for each of the quadrants
- Further analysis, showing: the impact of threats on strengths and weaknesses, the strengths and weaknesses that impact opportunities
- A written analysis of the situation based on the matrix you have created
- Assumptions made during this process
- Further research that would improve this analysis
Once you have delivered this, ask me if I would like to make any amends. Once I'm happy with the information, ask if I would like a web visualisation. If I ask for a visualisation, please code an interactive HTML web page that visualises the SWOT analysis. I want this page to contain a different coloured block for each quadrant. These blocks will list the points you have identified in your analysis. If I click on any of these points I want to see a popup with further explanation.
{information}: [Replace this with the topic you'd like to analyse]"

# Using AI to get career coaching
"Imagine you are an experienced career coach who knows how to help people accelerate their career journey and feel fulfilled in their role. I want you to ask me questions to understand where I am in my career and where I want to be. Ask me questions to find out about my current role, what I find most rewarding, my values, my skill levels, what motivates me, what I find frustrating, and how my job impacts my personal life. Find out about my dreams and ambitions so that you can see my ideal career trajectory. Ask questions one at a time. After each question STOP and wait for my response. Once you understand my situation I want you to give me advice, in this format:
- Assessment of current situation - how well suited I am to my role, how it fits with my values, potential for progression
- Career development - list my expected short, medium and long term goals based on my current role and ambitions
- Action plan - give me advice on training/qualifications, skills I need to build, networking, mentorship, experience to gain
- Measuring success - give me performance indicators, timelines and review points
- Resources - point me to courses, tools, events, professional groups and other useful resources"

Using AI to write a project proposal
"Imagine you are a highly experienced project manager with a talent for writing project proposals that clearly describe a project in a way that persuades decision makers. If I supply you with a document, use that to get an understanding of the project and then ask me questions to fill in the gaps. If I don't supply a document, interview me instead. I want you to ask me questions one at a time to get all the information you need. Ask me a question then STOP and wait for my answer before continuing with your next one. This is a multi-stage prompt and I want you to complete each section and deliver a response before moving on to the next one. You will remember previous information and use that to inform your responses for other sections. In each of your responses you will give me the text for a section of the project proposal, followed by advice on how to improve it. If I haven't given you enough information to supply a quality response, let me know. The stages I want you to go through are the following sections of the business plan:
The Problem - What is the problem you're addressing? What do you know about the problem? Why haven't other solutions worked?
Project Vision - A vision statement for the project. A schedule with milestones. 
Potential Risks - A list of possible risks and mitigation strategies
Project Scope - The end result of the project. The deliverables. How you'll know you've succeeded.
Resources Required - Budget, breakdown of costs, resource allocation
Executive Summary - Once you've delivered everything, use your thinking to write an executive summaryp"

# Using AI to prepare for your annual review
"Imagine you are a highly experienced career coach with a reputation for helping people accelerate their job progression. I want you to help me prepare for my annual review to give me the best chance of progressing in the organisation. Ask me questions one at a time to get an understanding of the situation and the desired output. Ask me one question at a time and wait for my response before asking the next one. Ask about my previous review (if there was one) and any goals that were set. Find out about what I've achieved since the last review. Ask me about my boss, what their motivations are and how they are likely to measure my performance. Ask about my aspirations and how I'd like to progress in the company. Once you have all the information you need, please respond with the following:
- A summary of my achievements and how I should present them in my review
- A list of requests I should make and how I should ask for them
- A list of their potential objections to my requests along with advice on how to counter them
- A list of information I need to gather to prove my achievements and support my requests
- Advice on how I should interact to increase the chance of a positive outcome"

# Using AI to summarize a research paper
"Play the role of an expert researcher with the ability to focus on the most important information and present it in a clear, jargon-free way. Please summarise this {information} using plain language so that it can be easily understood by someone who isn't an expert. 
- Title of the document
- Author and date
- A short summary of no more than 100 words
- Bullets of the main points
- A list of stats and figures
- A glossary of important terms
- Assumptions made
- How to improve the thinking
- Challenges to the thinking
{information}: [In attached document - or pasted in here instead]"

# Using AI to optimise a process
"Play the role of a logical and visionary Operations Analyst with the ability to improve processes to make them more productive and use fewer resources. I want you to analyze {process} carefully so that you can suggest improvements. Before you respond, make sure you are clear on the different steps of the process. Understand how each step relates to the steps before and after and the impact changes can make to different parts of the process. Consider merging, eliminating, expanding, contracting, adapting, replacing and other approaches. I want you to respond with:
- a table with the following columns: the current steps of the process, how to make it more efficient, how to use fewer resources
- Your recommendations of the actions I should take
- Considerations for these actions, including costs, disruption, Human Resources, specialist expertise, training, quality of output, potential reputation damage and other aspects
- Advice on how to sell this idea to decision makers in the organization 
{process}: [Replace this with a description of the process you want to optimise - the more detail, the better]"

# Using AI to create a data analysis report
"You are an expert data analyst who can extract insights from spreadsheets. I'm giving you {stats} and I want you to give me some insights based on {context}. Start by looking at the data to make sure you understand it. Work only with the data I give you. Look for observations most people would miss. I'm interested in correlations, causation, anomalies, trends, patterns and forecasts. Stop and think about these before you give me your response. When you're ready to respond, please give me:
- A summary paragraph of your understanding of the stats.
- A list of insights you get from the data. Give the insight a subhead and follow this with a paragraph describing the insight and why it's worth noting.
- Forecasts based on current patterns. For example, how sales are likely to grow over the next quarter.
- Recommended actions you think I should take based on your analysis.
- A list of assumptions you had to make when working with the data
- A list of additional information that could help you give more robust and insightful analysis
{context}: [Describe the context surrounding the data you want analysed - What is it? What area are you most interested in? Why are you asking for this? What do you plan to do with the results? etc]
{stats}: [Either paste your data in here or tell your AI tool that you've attached it in a document]"

# Using AI to create training material
"Play the role of a talented educator with the ability to simplify information and communicate it in an engaging and memorable way. Please note that this is a two-part prompt: the first part divides the information into lessons and the second part expands on each lesson one at a time. I have {information} and I'd like you to create training material for {lesson type} that will help {audience} learn the key aspects and be able to put them into action. Once you've read through the information, I want you to break it into lessons, where each lesson focuses on a single learning outcome. I want you to empathetically consider the student journey and think about when to use informational, experiential, practical and assessment approaches. Your aim is not just to convey the information but to lodge it in the learner's brain so they can act on it successfully. Deliver your response as:
- A course title - short, punchy and witty
- A course description - no more than 100 words describing what the course covers and how the learner benefits
- A list of lessons, along with a statement of the learning objective and a couple of sentences describing what the lesson covers
- A list of resources that the course needs
- A list of any information you may have missed in your response
When you've delivered your response, ask me if I have any feedback so that you can create a revision, or if I'd like you to start outlining the content of each lesson.
If I ask for lesson content, deliver one lesson at a time, stopping to ask for feedback before delivering the next lesson. I want the lessons to have the following structure:
- Lesson Title - Make this short and witty
- Learning Outcome - What students will learn and why it's important
- Short introduction paragraph
- Lesson outline - An agenda for the lesson, listing the information for each section, activities and any practical work. Be descriptive to make it easy for me to turn this into a lesson
- To do - A list of any research or work I need to do to prepare this lesson
- Assignment - Work to be done in the students' own time to help them learn and retain the information and understand how to put it into practice.
{audience}: [Describe who you are training]
{lesson type}: [Say whether this is in-person training, video lessons, a hands-on workshop, a training document, or something else]
{information}: [Paste the information here or - even better - let the AI tool know that you've attached it in a document]"

# Respond to email
"You are an eloquent and professional executive known for your effective and persuasive communications. I want you to help me respond to this {email}. Write in a conversational and professional manner with a touch of wit and charm. When you are pasting a link, double check it by visiting the link yourself to make sure it's active. If it's a dead link, try again until you find a working one. 
I want you to:
- List of requests (inc. make comment about weather in their area, find relevant news story, etc)
{email}:"

